    <section class="brand--department-for-business-innovation-skills organisation__margin-bottom" id="org-contacts">
  <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--border-top-5 brand--department-for-business-innovation-skills brand__border-color">Contact the Insolvency Service</h2>


    <div class="organisation__contact-section organisation__contact-section--border-top">
    <h3 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--font-size-19 gem-c-heading--padding  ">Insolvency enquiry line</h3>


    <div class="grid-row">

        <div class="column-two-thirds">

            <div class="organisation__margin-bottom">
                <p><a class="brand__color" href="http://www.insolvencydirect.bis.gov.uk/contactus/general.htm">Contact Form: Insolvency enquiry line</a></p>
            </div>

            <div class="organisation__margin-bottom">
                <p>Telephone</p>
                <p class="organisation__contact-number">0300 678 0015</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <p>For information about the insolvency process contact the Insolvency Enquiry Line during office hours. Open 9am to 5pm Monday to Friday except Wednesday 10am to 5pm. We can give you general information about: insolvency, what official receivers do and where you can go to get the information or advice you need.<br></br><br></br>We can’t give you: legal or financial advice, information on specific insolvency cases, information or advice on matters directly relating to other government departments.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="organisation__contact-section organisation__contact-section--border-top">
    <h3 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--font-size-19 gem-c-heading--padding  ">Redundancy Payments</h3>


    <div class="grid-row">
        <address class="column-half organisation__margin-bottom organisation__address">
            PO Box 16685<br></br>Birmingham<br></br>B2 2LX<br></br>United Kingdom<br></br>
        </address>

        <div class="column-half">


            <div class="organisation__margin-bottom">
                <p>Telephone</p>
                <p class="organisation__contact-number">0330 331 0020</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <p>Contact Redundancy Payments during office hours. Open 9am to 5pm Monday to Friday except Wednesday 10:30am to 5pm. Contact about claims for redundancy, pay in lieu of notice, holiday pay, arrears of wages, protective award payments and lost pension contributions. <br></br><br></br>Online Claims Service: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/claim-redundancy" class="brand__color">https://www.gov.uk/claim-redundancy</a></p>
  </div>
  <div class="organisation__contact-section organisation__contact-section--border-top">
    <h3 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--font-size-19 gem-c-heading--padding  ">Investigations and Enforcement Services</h3>


    <div class="grid-row">
        <address class="column-half organisation__margin-bottom organisation__address">
            Intelligence Hub<br></br>The Insolvency Service <br></br>4th, Floor Cannon House<br></br>18 Priory Queensway<br></br>Birmingham<br></br>B4 6FD<br></br>United Kingdom<br></br>
        </address>

        <div class="column-half">

            <div class="organisation__margin-bottom">
                <p><a class="brand__color" href="https://www.gov.uk/complain-company">Contact Form: Investigations and Enforcement Services</a></p>
            </div>

            <div class="organisation__margin-bottom">
                <p>Telephone</p>
                <p class="organisation__contact-number">0300 678 0017</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <p>The Insolvency Service Investigations and Enforcement Services(<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/insolvency-service-investigations-and-enforcement-what-we-do-our-outcomes-and-complaints" class="brand__color">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/insolvency-service-investigations-and-enforcement-what-we-do-our-outcomes-and-complaints</a>)  are responsible for investigating serious financial misconduct in companies and individuals who are subject to bankruptcy or debt relief orders. These powers to investigate are civil and not criminal.<br></br><br></br>Our independent Criminal Enforcement Team (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/insolvency-service-criminal-enforcement-team" class="brand__color">https://www.gov.uk/government/groups/insolvency-service-criminal-enforcement-team</a>)  is the lead criminal enforcement agency for insolvency related fraud and associated corporate misconduct.</p>
  </div>
